Project: Reveille

Purpose: Go service for waking stopped homelab containers behind Traefik.

Core behavior:
- Traefik calls Reveille through `forwardAuth`.
- Reveille starts stopped targets through Dockhand API.
- Wait page offers lease durations plus `Never`.
- Wait page polls status every 5s, then redirects when healthy.
- Finite leases stop the target again through Dockhand when they expire.

Implementation direction:
- Use Go for the server, Dockhand client, config, leases, scheduler, templates,
  and embedded assets.
- Use the current stable Go toolchain pinned in `go.mod` and CI. As of
  2026-05-19 this project targets Go 1.26 with toolchain go1.26.3.
- Keep dependencies current before release work. Check with `go list -m -u all`;
  `gopkg.in/yaml.v3 v3.0.1` is the current YAML parser dependency.
- Use plain HTML/CSS/vanilla JS for the wait page; no Node frontend needed.

Read first:
- `README.md`
- `docs/behavior.md`
- `.workflow/handoff.md` temporary build handoff when present
